  {
    q: "Why does my Bosch 24\" compact washer keep leaking?",
    a: "The most common cause on 24\" compact Bosch washers is a torn door boot seal — the rubber bellows gasket between the tub and the door. This seal tears when the drum is consistently overstuffed. The 24\" compact drum is 2.2 cubic feet — significantly smaller than a full-size washer — and homeowners accustomed to full-size machines often load it beyond capacity. Repeated overloading flexes the boot seal at the bottom fold until it tears. Replacing the boot seal solves the leak, and we explain load capacity before we leave every time we make this repair."
  },
