    q: "My Bosch dishwasher dishes have white film even on a clean cycle. What's wrong?",
    a: "White mineral film on dishes is a hard water issue combined with insufficient descaling. SoCal water — especially in Orange County, the Conejo Valley, and the San Fernando Valley — has high mineral content. The heating element and spray arms accumulate scale that reduces cleaning efficiency. Adding extra detergent makes scaling worse, not better. The fix: citric acid descaling cycle monthly, consistent rinse-aid every cycle, quarterly filter cleaning. If the E09 fault code appears, the heating element has scaled to the point of failure and needs replacement."
  },
