  <section class="brand-intro">
    <div class="brand-intro-inner">
      <h2>What We See on Bosch Calls Across Southern California</h2>
      <p>Bosch has become one of the most popular appliance brands in SoCal. Their dishwashers are the top sellers in the US, and we see them everywhere — the 24" compact 800 Series in West Hollywood and Santa Monica condos, the 500 Series in Irvine and Newport Beach family homes, the Benchmark refrigerators in Brentwood kitchen renovations.</p>
      <p>The dishwasher is where we spend most of our Bosch time, and the most important thing we've learned: E24, the most common error code, is almost never the drain pump. It's the filter. Bosch dishwashers have a filter assembly inside the tub that needs monthly cleaning. Most homeowners have never cleaned it and didn't know it exists. Three years of accumulated debris, one E24 error, one 45-minute service call, and a filter cleaning tutorial. No parts. That's the majority of our Bosch dishwasher calls.</p>
      <p>The second most common Bosch issue in SoCal is E09 — heating element failure from mineral scale. OC water, the SFV supply, and Calleguas in the Conejo Valley all have significant mineral content. Without regular descaling treatment, the element calcifies over 4-6 years. We replace it and explain how to prevent the next one.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

