  <section class="brand-context">
    <div class="brand-context-inner">
      <div class="section-number">06</div>
      <div class="brand-context-content">
        <h2>The Bosch Dishwasher Filter — Southern California's Most Missed Maintenance</h2>
        <p>Every Bosch dishwasher has a filter assembly inside the tub, under the lower spray arm. It consists of a cylindrical mesh filter and a flat microfilter beneath it. Together they catch food particles before they reach the drain pump. Bosch recommends cleaning the filter monthly. Most homeowners have never done it.</p>
        <p>The location isn't obvious. No external indicator, no light, no reminder. It's inside the tub at the bottom — twist the cylindrical filter counterclockwise, lift it out, then lift the flat microfilter below it. Rinse both under hot running water. Reinstall. Three minutes, once a month.</p>
        <p>When the filter is ignored for a year or more — which is most of what we see — food debris compacts in the mesh until water can't pass through. The dishwasher tries to drain, fails, and throws E24 or E22. We arrive, pull the filter, clean it, run a drain cycle. The machine works. We make sure every homeowner knows the filter location and monthly procedure before we leave.</p>

        <h2>Hard Water and Bosch Appliances in Southern California</h2>
        <p>Most of Southern California's water supply is hard — the Orange County Water District, LADWP blended supply, the Calleguas Municipal Water District in the Conejo Valley, and the SFV water supply all test hard to very hard.</p>
        <p>For Bosch dishwashers this creates two maintenance requirements. First: the heating element. Scale deposits build on the element's surface, reducing efficiency and eventually causing E09 failure. Running a monthly cycle with citric acid dishwasher cleaner dissolves scale before it accumulates to failure levels. A bottle of cleaner is $8. An E09 element replacement is $200+.</p>
        <p>Second: spray arm nozzles. Mineral deposits slowly block the small holes in the arms, reducing water coverage. The symptom is dishes that come out with food still on them. We descale spray arms on every Bosch dishwasher call in SoCal and check nozzle flow before we leave.</p>
        <p>The same dynamic affects Bosch refrigerators with water dispensers and ice makers. The inlet valve screen accumulates scale. The ice maker fill tube narrows. We check and clean the inlet valve screen on every Bosch refrigerator water system call.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

